Civil society groups are taking the government to court over the R350 grant applications. Neil Coleman from the Institute for Economic Justice discussed this with eNCA's Dan Moyane. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Civil society groups are taking government to court over the R350 grant applications. They claim some of the new regulations are unfair and should be declared unconstitutional. READ: COVID-19 grant | Reconsideration payments underway These new regulations disqualify applicants who have an income of more than R350. The activist groups claim the grant isn't enough to cover food and other expenses.